<ns3670:section xmlns:ns3670="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2se.security.tools.keytool.constructingACertificateChain">
    
    <ns3671:title xmlns:ns3671="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Constructing a certificate chain</ns3671:title>

<ns3672:para xmlns:ns3672="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">In the case of self-signed certificates the certificate authenticates the signer
of that same certificate.</ns3672:para>

<ns3673:para xmlns:ns3673="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">In the case of certificate chains each certificate in the chain authenticates
the signer of the previous certificate in that chain. There may be a number
of certificates in the chain with the topmost certificate often being signed
by a certificate authority which vouches for the identity of the next level
entity in the chain which, in turn, vouches for the next lower level.</ns3673:para>
</ns3670:section>